      <div class="rc"><span class="rc-icon">&#128293;</span><div class="rc-title">Smoke backing into the room</div><div class="rc-desc">If your Carlton fireplace is pushing smoke into the room, the flue is likely blocked or the draw has failed. Book a sweep.</div></div>
      <div class="rc"><span class="rc-icon">&#128168;</span><div class="rc-title">Soot smell through the fireplace</div><div class="rc-desc">A persistent soot or smoky smell in a Carlton home between burns usually means debris in the flue. A clean fixes it.</div></div>
      <div class="rc"><span class="rc-icon">&#9888;&#65039;</span><div class="rc-title">Over 12 months since the last clean</div><div class="rc-desc">Annual sweeping is the recommended standard for any fireplace used through winter. Book before the cold sets in.</div></div>
      <div class="rc"><span class="rc-icon">&#127968;</span><div class="rc-title">Just moved into a Carlton property</div><div class="rc-desc">Older Carlton homes often have fireplaces with no recent service history. Get it inspected before first use.</div></div>
